        "feedback": "The gasket groove construction is flawed. The code subtracts a full cylinder (r=25) from Z=14-16, then unions back a full cylinder (r=19) from Z=14-16. This union fills in the center bore (r=16) from Z=14 to Z=16, partially blocking it. The extra volume (~1,608 mm³) confirms this: expected ~59,790 mm³ vs actual 61,518 mm³. Fix: instead of subtract-outer/union-inner, create the groove as an annular ring directly. Use a workplane at Z=16, sketch two concentric circles (r=19 and r=25), extrude the ring between them downward 2mm, and cut that ring from the result. For example: groove = cq.Workplane('XY').workplane(offset=14).circle(25).circle(19).extrude(2) then result = result.cut(groove). This avoids any union that could fill the bore.",
